The Vice President, Mike Pence, announced that the Trump administration will not be retiring the USS Harry S. Truman. He stated that he spoke to President Trump, who made the decision to keep the ship in service. Pence highlighted the ship's history and contributions, including its involvement in destroying the territory of the ISIS caliphate and its support for NATO allies. He emphasized the importance of aircraft carriers in projecting force and stated that the administration is committed to a 350-ship Navy. Pence mentioned that the decision was made by the Commander-in-Chief and that they will seek bipartisan support for the $750 billion military budget. He also expressed confidence in maintaining the USS Truman while continuing to make investments for the safety and security of the American people.